org.apache.datasketches.pig.hll

Class UnionSketch

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.pig.EvalFunc<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>
      • org.apache.datasketches.pig.hll.UnionSketch
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.pig.Accumulator<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>, org.apache.pig.Algebraic

    public class UnionSketch
extends org.apache.pig.EvalFunc<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>
implements org.apache.pig.Accumulator<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>, org.apache.pig.Algebraic
    This is a Pig UDF that performs the Union operation on HllSketches. This class implements both the Accumulator and Algebraic interfaces.
    Author:
    Alexander Saydakov

      • exec

        public org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray exec(org.apache.pig.data.Tuple inputTuple)
                                       throws IOException
        Top-level exec function. This method accepts an input Tuple containing a Bag of one or more inner Sketch Tuples and returns a single serialized HllSketch as a DataByteArray. Sketch Tuple is a Tuple containing a single DataByteArray (BYTEARRAY in Pig), which is a serialized HllSketch.
        Specified by:

      • accumulate

        public void accumulate(org.apache.pig.data.Tuple inputTuple)
                throws IOException
        An Accumulator version of the standard exec() method. Like exec(), accumulator is called with a bag of Sketch Tuples. Unlike exec(), it doesn't serialize the result at the end. Instead, it can be called multiple times, each time with another bag of Sketch Tuples to be input to the union.
        Specified by:
        accumulate in interface org.apache.pig.Accumulator<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>
        Parameters:
        inputTuple - A tuple containing a single bag, containing Sketch Tuples.
        Throws:
        IOException - by Pig
        See Also:
        exec(org.apache.pig.data.Tuple), "org.apache.pig.Accumulator.accumulate(org.apache.pig.data.Tuple)"
